message: Focus on cooking raw proteins and vegetables with the stove first. Then, combine a cooked protein with a grain (like cooked egg and tortilla, or cooked beans and rice) for a good base value. You can often add one cooked vegetable to this combination to further increase the value. Be careful with adding too many ingredients; combining four or more items, especially if they're already complex, often results in 'overcomplicated' items with zero or negative value. I found 2 or 3 ingredients to be the sweet spot for maximum value. Avoid using water on cooked or combined items, as it consistently led to negative outcomes.
